                <position book_orientation="0" place="head">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Maior dehinc bellorum moles, et acta grandiora. Immanes, diriq[ue] hostes pro suis viribus, Samnites: 
                        sed Pyrrhus, et Annibal, quàm periti, absolutiq[ue] Duces; quàm sa[e]vi, ac terribiles bellatores?
                    </marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Samnites"/>
                    <person name="Pyrrhus of Epirus"/>
                    <person name="Hannibal"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The burden of wars became larger and the actions mightier from this time on. The Samnites: fierce and horrible enemies in 
                view of their strength. Yet how skilled and perfect leaders Pyrrhus and Hannibal were, how ferocious and terrifying warriors?
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
